-2-1920x1155.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fezzari-Solitude-carbon-hardtail-mountain-bike-2021-2-698x420.jpg 698w\"></a></p><p>The head angle is much slacker at 68º, and reach is longer, giving it more modern handling and capable descending. The angles aren’t as dramatic as on their recent full suspension mountain bikes, like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/10/31/review-fezzari-delano-peak-brings-big-trail-talent-to-a-mid-travel-mountain-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Delano Peak</a> and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/08/17/first-ride-fezzari-la-sal-peak-29er-enduro-bike-bombs-drops-rips-climbs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">La Sal Peak</a>, but appropriate for a hardtail.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fezzari-Solitude-carbon-hardtail-mountain-bike-2021-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fezzari-Solitude-carbon-hardtail-mountain-bike-2021-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1371\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fezzari-Solitude-carbon-hardtail-mountain-bike-2021-3.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fezzari-Solitude-carbon-hardtail-mountain-bike-2021-3.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fezzari-Solitude-carbon-hardtail-mountain-bike-2021-3-297x212.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fezzari-Solitude-carbon-hardtail-mountain-bike-2021-3-800x571.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02